1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,020
The bulk of us who are under 60 here, to love on them.

2
00:00:05,010 --> 00:00:10,870
It's their faithfulness, their commitment, their sacrifice for all these years that allow us to be where we are.

3
00:00:11,570 --> 00:00:14,270
And as we go forward in ministry, we're building on their shoulders.

4
00:00:14,930 --> 00:00:17,630
And we want to acknowledge and honor and bless them.

5
00:00:17,630 --> 00:00:24,830
So under 60, we pay $3 and we get to serve them and love them and give them the standing ovation.

6
00:00:25,250 --> 00:00:28,090
But you are all welcome. We want the whole church to be there.

7
00:00:28,090 --> 00:00:30,750
and we'll proclaim God is good together

8
00:00:30,750 --> 00:00:33,050
as we love those who've gone before us.

9
00:00:33,250 --> 00:00:34,730
So look forward to having you there next week.

10
00:00:35,430 --> 00:00:38,870
Well, this morning we continue in a four-week series

11
00:00:38,870 --> 00:00:41,710
talking about our money and our stewardship.

12
00:00:41,910 --> 00:00:43,450
And if you were a guest this morning,

13
00:00:43,770 --> 00:00:45,550
you picked a great time to come

14
00:00:45,550 --> 00:00:48,190
because we're now talking about money.

15
00:00:48,610 --> 00:00:49,630
And let's just be honest.

16
00:00:49,710 --> 00:00:52,510
If you're a guest this morning, this is family business.

17
00:00:52,510 --> 00:00:55,710
This is something that those who are committed to this church

18
00:00:55,710 --> 00:00:57,110
are going to wrestle with together.

19
00:00:57,110 --> 00:01:01,110
and we welcome you to look in and peer into what's going on,

20
00:01:01,370 --> 00:01:06,410
but we don't want you to feel guilty or any compunction to give or anything to this place

21
00:01:06,410 --> 00:01:08,670
until God leads you to that place.

22
00:01:09,510 --> 00:01:14,890
So just enjoy, relax, and the rest of us, we're going to scour God's Word for truth today

23
00:01:14,890 --> 00:01:18,490
and enjoy Him and look forward to what He's going to speak to us about.

24
00:01:18,490 --> 00:01:26,530
I want this series to be life-transforming and real, make it a difference in our lives.

25
00:01:27,540 --> 00:01:30,480
Scripture is full of references about money.

26
00:01:30,580 --> 00:01:33,120
In fact, there are over 2,000 verses on the topic.

27
00:01:33,920 --> 00:01:37,660
The Bible talks so much about money because it's so dear to us.

28
00:01:37,760 --> 00:01:38,940
It's so dear to our heart.

29
00:01:39,300 --> 00:01:41,640
It reflects what we care about.

30
00:01:42,260 --> 00:01:43,560
It reflects our spirit.

31
00:01:44,160 --> 00:01:50,310
It's a vehicle for us to worship the Lord or to determine what we truly do worship.

32
00:01:51,290 --> 00:01:54,670
I was a pastor that was very afraid of speaking about money.

33
00:01:55,190 --> 00:01:56,790
It felt self-serving.

34
00:01:57,110 --> 00:02:02,130
It felt manipulative with all the scandals of our past.

35
00:02:02,250 --> 00:02:04,110
I just felt like I couldn't go there.

36
00:02:04,510 --> 00:02:07,010
So for years, I rarely talked about it.

37
00:02:07,490 --> 00:02:12,980
And I got really emboldened on this topic when I took Crown Ministries.

38
00:02:13,500 --> 00:02:21,940
When I went through the course, the 12 weeks of studying God's Word on all these various dimensions of money and stewardship and finances,

39
00:02:22,580 --> 00:02:24,660
it just turned my head around.

40
00:02:25,940 --> 00:02:28,900
And so I'm not asking you all to go through it to be preachers,

41
00:02:29,240 --> 00:02:31,620
but I'll tell you, when you go through that course,

42
00:02:31,720 --> 00:02:37,500
it will change your whole world view about how God views money and our response to it.

43
00:02:37,920 --> 00:02:40,200
Robin and I are going to lead a study this coming year,

44
00:02:40,540 --> 00:02:43,440
and there's others in the congregation that will be doing so as well.

45
00:02:43,440 --> 00:02:45,740
I would encourage you to dive into one of those.

46
00:02:46,160 --> 00:02:47,500
You can do it for 12 weeks,

47
00:02:47,700 --> 00:02:52,980
and I guarantee you're going to be blessed and encouraged and really have a good time.

48
00:02:53,840 --> 00:02:59,160
So that's why I'm so passionate, because I've seen God, in His Word, talk about this topic.

49
00:02:59,540 --> 00:03:02,320
And I want to preach with passion and power this morning.

50
00:03:02,680 --> 00:03:08,030
What I want from you is I want you to be passionate about three things.

51
00:03:08,030 --> 00:03:11,350
The first is living for giving.

52
00:03:12,280 --> 00:03:18,380
I want you to be passionate about living that you might be a blessing to others, that you might live for giving.

53
00:03:18,780 --> 00:03:22,800
Number two, I want you to be passionate about living through giving.

54
00:03:23,300 --> 00:03:31,360
And finally, I want you to be passionate about a lifestyle we're going to call giving living.

55
00:03:32,870 --> 00:03:38,180
It's easy to remember, catchy almost, makes a great sermon title,

56
00:03:38,180 --> 00:03:41,180
but it better it makes a life.

57
00:03:42,210 --> 00:03:45,570
And I want us to live a lifestyle of giving living.

58
00:03:46,730 --> 00:03:50,250
As we've been talking about, when you adopt a giving living lifestyle,

59
00:03:50,730 --> 00:03:56,010
you're getting in touch with living as Jesus would live, and that's a life of giving.

60
00:03:56,010 --> 00:04:01,640
The Bible says in John 3.16, God so loved the world that he did what?

61
00:04:01,900 --> 00:04:03,040
He gave.

62
00:04:04,060 --> 00:04:11,200
It's the character and heart of our God to be generous, even to the point of sacrificing his own son.

63
00:04:12,400 --> 00:04:13,540
That's giving living.

64
00:04:14,380 --> 00:04:15,800
That's a God who's generous.

65
00:04:16,700 --> 00:04:23,300
And giving living is not just something we can do as individuals, but it's something here for the church as well.

66
00:04:23,720 --> 00:04:25,600
See, we know the verses.

67
00:04:26,460 --> 00:04:28,620
1 Corinthians 9, I've shared it with you.

68
00:04:28,900 --> 00:04:31,140
For God loves the person who gives with a frown.

69
00:04:33,130 --> 00:04:33,370
No.

70
00:04:34,510 --> 00:04:37,390
God loves the person who gives cheerfully.

71
00:04:38,930 --> 00:04:41,330
The word in Greek has to do with the word hilarious.

72
00:04:43,110 --> 00:04:46,390
I'd love to see us smile when we give.

73
00:04:49,640 --> 00:04:52,960
Some week we're going to try some exercise to see what that's about.

74
00:04:53,650 --> 00:04:57,670
Instead of putting our head down and pass the plate, we're going to give with joy.

75
00:04:59,920 --> 00:05:00,560
We know the verse.

76
00:05:00,640 --> 00:05:01,400
We also know this one.

77
00:05:01,400 --> 00:05:03,980
1 Timothy 6, verse 10.

78
00:05:04,260 --> 00:05:08,700
For the love of money is at the root of all kinds of evil.

79
00:05:09,020 --> 00:05:13,540
It doesn't say that money is the root of all evil, does it?

80
00:05:14,280 --> 00:05:16,360
People say that all the time.

81
00:05:16,440 --> 00:05:17,780
Well, you know money is the root of all evil.

82
00:05:18,300 --> 00:05:18,680
Really?

83
00:05:20,050 --> 00:05:22,490
And I suppose that God helps those who help themselves, right?

84
00:05:22,570 --> 00:05:23,390
And they go, yeah, exactly.

85
00:05:23,450 --> 00:05:23,910
It's in the Bible.

86
00:05:24,350 --> 00:05:25,070
No, it's not.

87
00:05:26,140 --> 00:05:27,180
That was Thomas Jefferson.

88
00:05:29,280 --> 00:05:32,960
God, thank God, helps those who can't help themselves, like us.

89
00:05:33,640 --> 00:05:39,280
Amen? Love of money is at the root of all evil.

90
00:05:39,680 --> 00:05:42,680
Money's not the problem, it's our attitude towards it.

91
00:05:43,140 --> 00:05:46,340
And if we love it and hoard it, that's the problem.

92
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:51,420
And some people, it says, craving money, have wandered from the faith

93
00:05:51,420 --> 00:05:54,740
and pierced themselves with many sorrows.

94
00:05:55,870 --> 00:05:58,670
They craved it. They couldn't let it go.

95
00:05:58,670 --> 00:06:01,470
They had to have more. When's enough? It's never enough.

96
00:06:02,960 --> 00:06:04,980
Because there's always somebody else who has more than you.

97
00:06:04,980 --> 00:06:08,390
and you will chase the rest of your life

98
00:06:08,390 --> 00:06:10,070
trying to catch up with the Joneses.

99
00:06:10,370 --> 00:06:12,070
The Joneses don't exist, friends,

100
00:06:13,660 --> 00:06:15,020
because there's always some Jones

101
00:06:15,020 --> 00:06:16,020
better than that Jones.

102
00:06:16,140 --> 00:06:16,820
You see what I'm saying?

103
00:06:17,080 --> 00:06:18,240
You can always chase

104
00:06:18,240 --> 00:06:19,860
and you'll never get there.

105
00:06:23,020 --> 00:06:24,140
We know what God wants.

106
00:06:24,220 --> 00:06:25,520
We know God wants us to give.

107
00:06:25,680 --> 00:06:27,740
We know God wants us to give to the church.

108
00:06:27,980 --> 00:06:29,260
We know we're supposed to tithe.

109
00:06:29,500 --> 00:06:30,080
We just say,

110
00:06:30,080 --> 00:06:31,520
Pastor, I'm still thinking about it.

111
00:06:32,240 --> 00:06:33,240
I'm thinking about it.

112
00:06:34,200 --> 00:06:35,100
And it's been 10 years.

113
00:06:35,200 --> 00:06:36,240
I'm still thinking about it,

114
00:06:36,260 --> 00:06:37,340
but I'm thinking about it.

115
00:06:37,360 --> 00:06:38,220
Every year you preach

116
00:06:38,220 --> 00:06:39,380
and I'm thinking about it.

117
00:06:39,760 --> 00:06:42,220
It's time for us to stop thinking and just start doing.

118
00:06:43,180 --> 00:06:44,000
And just do it.

119
00:06:44,300 --> 00:06:45,380
And trust the Lord.

120
00:06:45,680 --> 00:06:46,620
He's going to take care of us.

121
00:06:46,860 --> 00:06:49,840
One of our problems, though, is not only are we thinking about it,

122
00:06:50,000 --> 00:06:52,020
but we get caught up with Stuff Mart.

123
00:06:54,530 --> 00:06:55,590
You know what Stuff Mart is?

124
00:06:56,650 --> 00:07:01,910
Stuff Mart is the proverbial Costco, Sam's Club, Big Five, Nordstrom's,

125
00:07:02,010 --> 00:07:03,530
kind of all rolled into one.

126
00:07:04,640 --> 00:07:06,860
And it's so a part of our culture, isn't it?

127
00:07:06,860 --> 00:07:10,720
We've got to go to Stuff Mart and get more stuff to pack our homes

128
00:07:10,720 --> 00:07:13,600
and stay busy and never connect with people

129
00:07:13,600 --> 00:07:17,060
and chase more hours at work and do more things,

130
00:07:17,240 --> 00:07:18,580
we get more stuff.

131
00:07:20,320 --> 00:07:22,480
And then if we get around to it, we'll give to the Lord.

132
00:07:22,580 --> 00:07:23,180
But guess what?

133
00:07:23,240 --> 00:07:25,280
Those credit card payments are piling up

134
00:07:25,280 --> 00:07:28,200
and I guess the Lord doesn't get any of his due this month

135
00:07:28,200 --> 00:07:29,900
because it's going to Stuff Mart.

136
00:07:32,270 --> 00:07:35,210
The VeggieTales teach us about Stuff Mart.

137
00:07:37,000 --> 00:07:37,580
Let's take a look.

138
00:07:37,580 --> 00:07:53,060
What does it mean?

139
00:07:58,850 --> 00:07:59,570
It's big.

140
00:08:02,940 --> 00:08:05,880
Madam, there's someone here to see you.

141
00:08:12,360 --> 00:08:13,080
Ourselves.

142
00:08:13,280 --> 00:08:15,200
We moved in down the street.

143
00:08:16,440 --> 00:08:21,280
Some say we're the most delightful bunch of fellows you'll ever want to meet.

144
00:08:22,520 --> 00:08:29,760
And if you have a moment to spare, find lady with beauty so rare.

145
00:08:30,730 --> 00:08:36,810
We'd like to take a minute or two on a topic of interest to you.

146
00:08:36,810 --> 00:08:43,610
We represent the Stuff Mart, an enormous land of goodies.

147
00:08:43,890 --> 00:08:45,790
Would you mind if we stepped in, please?

148
00:08:47,800 --> 00:08:54,560
And as associates of the Stuff Mart, it looks like you could use some stuff.

149
00:08:54,800 --> 00:09:28,480
Oh, yes, I was just saying that I pray that you won't take this reservation as a custom.

150
00:09:28,480 --> 00:10:43,920
Of the wonderful yet to come.

151
00:10:45,440 --> 00:10:50,800
Pictures you keep are so nice, but you really do.

152
00:10:50,800 --> 00:10:57,200
Happiness waits at the stuff mart.

153
00:10:58,180 --> 00:11:01,440
All you need is lots more stuff.

154
00:11:01,860 --> 00:11:15,240
I think that's true.

155
00:11:16,200 --> 00:11:17,420
Yes, it is.

156
00:11:17,880 --> 00:11:46,320
Happiness waits at the stuff mart.

157
00:11:47,260 --> 00:12:03,440
All you need is lots more stuff.

158
00:12:03,440 --> 00:12:06,660
Happiness waits at the stuff mart.

159
00:12:08,430 --> 00:12:10,730
And can't you just see that moral tension?

160
00:12:11,250 --> 00:12:12,830
Is this really true?

161
00:12:13,830 --> 00:12:15,130
It's not true.

162
00:12:16,690 --> 00:12:18,590
The more stuff, the more clutter,

163
00:12:18,590 --> 00:12:22,850
the more your credit card goes up, but you're really not happy.

164
00:12:24,550 --> 00:12:28,650
I can't find a rhyme there, but, you know, the reality is this.

165
00:12:29,640 --> 00:12:33,230
Stuff gets in the way of our giving to the Lord.

166
00:12:34,620 --> 00:12:39,040
It's a pseudo-tranquilizer that makes us feel good for the moment,

167
00:12:40,040 --> 00:12:41,680
but it's just stuff.

168
00:12:42,960 --> 00:12:46,440
And friends, I'm here to say that our culture is so embedded in materialism,

169
00:12:46,440 --> 00:12:50,420
our culture is so embedded in individualism,

170
00:12:50,420 --> 00:12:54,880
that those things program us to be wealthy and yet isolated.

171
00:12:56,210 --> 00:13:00,730
We work more hours and crave to get more per hour

172
00:13:00,730 --> 00:13:03,890
that we can then work harder to get more stuff.

173
00:13:06,020 --> 00:13:08,560
And we become rich and lonely in the process.

174
00:13:10,010 --> 00:13:13,290
Robin and I are very convicted that our suburban lifestyle,

175
00:13:13,590 --> 00:13:16,230
which drives us to more stuff and loneliness,

176
00:13:16,590 --> 00:13:19,150
is keeping us from the very people in our own neighborhood.

177
00:13:20,740 --> 00:13:23,980
It's really easy for us just to get up and go and fly

178
00:13:23,980 --> 00:13:27,580
and literally maybe once or twice a year connect with a neighbor

179
00:13:27,580 --> 00:13:32,020
because we're driven, aren't we, on this lifestyle of get more stuff

180
00:13:32,020 --> 00:13:35,080
and then buy it, take it home, and cocoon in the home,

181
00:13:35,160 --> 00:13:37,820
behind the gates, away from other people.

182
00:13:39,460 --> 00:13:41,360
And I buy into that as easy as anybody else,

183
00:13:41,500 --> 00:13:42,980
and I get really challenged by that.

184
00:13:43,970 --> 00:13:46,250
And somewhere the Christian church needs to say,

185
00:13:46,430 --> 00:13:50,910
no, we love our country, we love the opportunity,

186
00:13:50,910 --> 00:13:56,370
We love all the opportunity for the stuff, but we have to say no to a mindset that says,

187
00:13:56,770 --> 00:13:59,850
stuff will make me happy, so charge it up.

188
00:14:01,300 --> 00:14:06,420
Pay for it later, worry about it later, and when God comes calling for the tithe,

189
00:14:06,520 --> 00:14:08,680
we say, Lord, we don't have any left.

190
00:14:09,500 --> 00:14:10,760
We chase the stuff.

191
00:14:13,450 --> 00:14:19,790
How about we be a little less rich and a little more deeply connected to each other?

192
00:14:20,980 --> 00:14:24,380
How about we be deeply connected to God and each other?

193
00:14:24,660 --> 00:14:26,460
That's a giving, living lifestyle.

194
00:14:28,030 --> 00:14:31,190
We give of ourselves and to the Lord.

195
00:14:31,770 --> 00:14:33,770
And we may have a little less stuff,

196
00:14:35,180 --> 00:14:38,700
but I think in the end, we're more fulfilled, really,

197
00:14:41,730 --> 00:14:43,650
to live a lifestyle of giving, living.

198
00:14:43,650 --> 00:14:45,990
We're going to have to say no to Stuff Mart sometimes.

199
00:14:47,100 --> 00:14:47,680
Let's be honest.

200
00:14:47,800 --> 00:14:51,440
When I go to Stuff Mart, you go in for one item.

201
00:14:52,350 --> 00:14:53,770
You come out with ten, don't you?

202
00:14:53,770 --> 00:14:58,270
because you needed 64 gallons of mayonnaise at a special deal.

203
00:14:58,850 --> 00:15:01,090
You need to have thus and such.

204
00:15:01,490 --> 00:15:04,890
And we rationalize and tell ourselves rational lies,

205
00:15:05,110 --> 00:15:10,270
and we walk out of there with $150 more than we thought for the $2 item we went in for

206
00:15:10,270 --> 00:15:13,310
because it's there in our face.

207
00:15:13,770 --> 00:15:14,110
You know what?

208
00:15:14,150 --> 00:15:15,570
Just don't go there for a while.

209
00:15:18,710 --> 00:15:23,710
When we expose ourselves to more things, we become enraptured by the things we don't have.

210
00:15:24,680 --> 00:15:25,320
Just don't go.

211
00:15:26,020 --> 00:15:27,260
You won't even know what you're missing.

212
00:15:28,650 --> 00:15:29,630
And don't take your children.

213
00:15:29,790 --> 00:15:31,470
It's over when you bring them in there.

214
00:15:33,400 --> 00:15:34,060
Food for thought.

215
00:15:34,800 --> 00:15:36,880
We're going to have to live a lifestyle of giving, living.

216
00:15:36,880 --> 00:15:40,960
We're going to have to live, first of all, as God is our source.

217
00:15:44,190 --> 00:15:48,310
The Bible says that God created the heavens and the earth.

218
00:15:49,050 --> 00:15:50,910
Therefore, everything is his.

219
00:15:51,230 --> 00:15:52,690
Psalm 24, it says that.

220
00:15:53,010 --> 00:15:55,790
The earth is the Lord's and everything in it,

221
00:15:55,790 --> 00:15:59,370
The world and all its people belong to Him.

222
00:16:00,190 --> 00:16:04,410
If God made everything, God is our creator, then He is our provider.

223
00:16:05,190 --> 00:16:08,730
And He's the one in whom we live and move and have our being.

224
00:16:12,080 --> 00:16:15,160
Therefore, friends, He owns it all.

225
00:16:16,850 --> 00:16:20,710
He's actually the purveyor of Stuff Mart in one sense.

226
00:16:21,030 --> 00:16:22,190
He owns everything.

227
00:16:23,580 --> 00:16:26,340
It doesn't mean that we have to have everything.

228
00:16:27,880 --> 00:16:30,960
We are to manage what He allows us to have,

229
00:16:30,960 --> 00:16:36,320
and we must be wise in how we take in what we take and what we have.

230
00:16:38,170 --> 00:16:42,810
Do we give the Lord His firstfruits and then go and bless our friends and our families?

231
00:16:43,010 --> 00:16:48,610
Or do we bless ourselves by trying to be happy first and then rip off God in the process?

232
00:16:50,370 --> 00:16:56,670
We're going to have to realize that God is the source and live and trust Him to provide for us

233
00:16:56,670 --> 00:16:59,150
When we give him, let's first do him.

234
00:17:00,520 --> 00:17:01,320
It's all his.

235
00:17:03,640 --> 00:17:07,220
In fact, with God as our provider, if we live that way, we can afford to be generous

236
00:17:07,220 --> 00:17:09,720
because we're not going to worry about it coming in.

237
00:17:10,100 --> 00:17:12,480
You know, I think God gives more so we can bless others.

238
00:17:13,040 --> 00:17:18,280
But if we take in and then just buy stuff for us, I don't think he blesses that.

239
00:17:20,840 --> 00:17:24,220
We've found in our life the times we get more generous and give things away,

240
00:17:24,520 --> 00:17:26,300
God seems to provide more that we can keep giving.

241
00:17:28,330 --> 00:17:30,890
When we stop giving, the blessings dry up

242
00:17:30,890 --> 00:17:32,710
and we seem to just spend it all on ourselves

243
00:17:32,710 --> 00:17:35,510
and we get lonely and no more comes in.

244
